# Ortus

This project was bootstrapped with [Ortus](https://github.com/{{ github_username }}/ortus).

## What is Ortus?

Ortus is a project template that sets up:
- **Beads** (`bd`) - Local-first issue tracking
- **Ralph** - Autonomous task execution loop (default)
{%- if agent_cli == 'codex' %}
- **Goal** - Opt-in `/goal`-directive orchestrator (long-lived Codex session)
{%- else %}
- **Goal** - Opt-in `/goal`-directive orchestrator (long-lived Claude session)
{%- endif %}
- **Interview** - PRD generation through conversation

## Scripts

| Script | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `./ortus/ralph.sh` | Run the task implementation loop (default) |
{%- if agent_cli == 'codex' %}
| `./ortus/goal.sh` | Opt-in alternative: long-lived `codex exec "/goal CONDITION"` session |
{%- else %}
| `./ortus/goal.sh` | Opt-in alternative: long-lived `claude -p "/goal CONDITION"` session |
{%- endif %}
| `./ortus/idea.sh` | Quick-start a new feature |
| `./ortus/interview.sh` | Generate PRD through interview |
| `./ortus/tail.sh` | Watch ralph + goal logs |

`ralph.sh` and `goal.sh` share `.beads/ralph.flock`, so only one orchestrator can run at a time.
{%- if agent_cli == 'codex' %}

## Model

The default is **whatever the Codex CLI itself defaults to** — Ortus does not
pin a model name. Pinning one would go stale as soon as OpenAI moves that
default, and every project generated before the move would carry the old name.

To pin a model for this project, uncomment the `model` line in
`.codex/config.toml`:

```toml
model = "gpt-5-codex"
```

That file is the only place to set it; there is no `codex_model` copier
question to re-answer. For one run without editing it, export
`ORTUS_CODEX_MODEL`:

```bash
ORTUS_CODEX_MODEL=gpt-5-codex ./ortus/goal.sh "..."
```

Precedence: `ORTUS_CODEX_MODEL` > `.codex/config.toml` > the CLI's own default.
{%- endif %}

